research_municipality_step.notes: The City of River Oaks, TX operates under a mayor-council government type, also identified as a Home Rule government. The governing body consists of a mayor and five councilpersons, all elected at large. The mayor presides over council meetings and votes only in the event of a tie. Leigh Ann Turner also holds the role of Mayor Pro-Tem. The 'Place' numbers for council members refer to their specific seat on the council, not a geographical division.
